# Configuration Management Rules

## Configuration Files
- [config.yaml](mdc:config.yaml) - Main configuration file
- [config.example.yaml](mdc:config.example.yaml) - Example configuration template
- Use YAML format for configuration files
- Keep sensitive data in environment variables

## Configuration Structure
```yaml
# Database settings
database:
  host: localhost
  port: 5432
  name: market_insights

# API settings
api:
  host: 0.0.0.0
  port: 8000
  debug: false

# Data processing
data:
  providers: ["stooq", "yahoo"]
  output_path: "engine/out"
```

## Environment Variables
- Use `.env` files for local development
- Never commit sensitive data to version control
- Document all required environment variables
- Use consistent naming conventions (UPPER_SNAKE_CASE)

## Configuration Loading
- Load configuration at application startup
- Validate configuration values
- Provide sensible defaults
- Handle missing configuration gracefully

## Security Guidelines
- Never hardcode secrets in configuration files
- Use environment-specific configurations
- Implement proper secret management
- Validate configuration in production
